  schema:name "Mikhail Bakunin" ;
  schema:description "Mikhail Bakunin (1814–1876) was a Russian revolutionary and anarchist theorist who articulated the foundational anarchist critique of the state, including the argument that revolutionary seizure of state power inevitably reproduces domination." ;
